<item>
            <title>[LU-3588] use lctl --device option to specify device for LFSCK</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3588</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl lfsck_start --device DDDD&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; option parsing is inconsistent with other lctl commands.  It would be more consistent to allow the device to be specified as an lctl option like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl --device DDDD lfsck_start&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; or in interactive mode using the &quot;device&quot; command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These set the &quot;lcfg_devname&quot; and &quot;cur_device&quot; global variables for lctl and can be used by all of the sub-commands.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
